:"1179","1135":"1135","1243":"1243","1219":"1219","Caulaincourt, 02490, Aisne, Picardie, France":"Caulaincourt, Aisne, Picardie, France","Caulaincourt, Aisne, Picardie, França":"Caulaincourt, Aisne, Picardie, France","Caulaincourt, Aisne, Picardie, France":"Caulaincourt, Aisne, Picardie, France","La Fère, Aisne, Picardie, França":"La Fère, Aisne, Picardie, France","nameMeanings":[{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"la","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Vietnamese Hung, Cuong, Anh, Thanh, Ha, Hoang, Tuan, Chau, Hao, Hien, Hoa, Hue, Nam, Phong, Sinh, Tuong, Min, Tam, Tanh, Thai, Tham, Tinh, Yeong.  Chinese Hong, Hang, Sang, Tong, Chan, Chi, Hwa Ja, Hyung, Kam, Ki Bong, Kin, Man.","Vietnamese: from the Chinese surname 羅, see   Luo   1.","Vietnamese (<b>Lã</b>): from the Chinese surname 呂, see   Lu   6 and 3 below."],"variants":[{"name":"Luo","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Chinese Wei, Jian, Yi, Ping, Yong, Zhen, Feng, Hong, Ming, Jin, Bin, Chen, Hai, Lan, Min, Huan, Hung, Shen, Tian.","Chinese:","Mandarin form of the surname 羅, meaning ‘net for catching birds’ or ‘to collect’ in Chinese: (i) from Luo (羅), the name of an ancient state (located in present-day Hubei province). After it was annexed by the state of Chu during the early Spring and Autumn period (770–476  BC ), people from the state migrated southwards and adopted Luo (羅) as their surname. (ii) from the Po Duo Luo (破多羅) and Chi Luo (叱羅) families from the Xianbei ethnic group in northern China, who changed their original surnames to 羅 during the Northern Wei dynasty (386–534  AD ). (iii) from the personal name Hu Se Luo (斛瑟羅), leader of an ancient Turkic tribe who are believed to have migrated to China during the Tang dynasty (618–907  AD ). His descendants inherited his name Hu Se Luo (斛瑟羅) as their surname and shortened it to 羅 during the Northern Wei dynasty (386–534  AD ). (iv) from the name of one of the seven families from the Bandun Man, an ethnic group residing in ancient southwestern China (located mainly in present-day Sichuan province)."]}]},{"name":"Fère","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Turkish: ornamental or topographic name from <i>dere</i> ‘brook’.","Indian (Maharashtra): Maratha name of unexplained etymology.","Chinese: variant Romanization of the surname 謝, see   Xie   1."],"variants":[{"name":"Xie","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Chinese: Hong, Li, Ming, Ying, Min, Qing, Yuan, Bin, Hui, Ping, Wei, Xiaoli, Ding, Chang, Lan, Quan, Cong, Dang, Hai, Tian, Yiping.","Chinese:","Mandarin form of the surname 謝, meaning ‘thank’ in Chinese: (i) from Xie (謝), the name of an ancient state (possibly located in Nanyang in Henan province), annexed around the Western Zhou dynasty (1046–771  BC ).Later this place was probably granted to Shen Bo (the Earl of Shen), uncle of King Xuan of Zhou (reigned 827–782  BC ). After it was annexed during the Spring and Autumn period (770–476  BC ), the name of the state was adopted as a surname. (ii) adopted in place of the surname Zhi-Le (直勒) by Xie Xiaozheng (謝孝政), an official during the Northern Qi dynasty (550–577  AD )."]}]},{"name":"Elise","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["short form of   Elisabeth .  The name was introduced into the English-speaking world (where it is often written without the accent) in the late 19th century and has become fairly popularity in recent years."],"variants":[{"name":"Elisa","meanings":["short form of   Elisabeth .  The name was introduced into the English-speaking world (where it is often written without the accent) in the late 19th century and has become fairly popularity in recent years."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Elise de la Fère was born in 1160, in La Fère, Aisne, Picardie, France, her father, Jean de la Fere, was 25 and her mother, Blanche de Roye, was 22. She married Baudouin de Caulincourt in 1180. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 2 daughters. She died in 1219, in Caulaincourt, Aisne, Picardie, France, at the age of 59."},"et":{"1160–1219":"1160–1219","1173–Female":"1173–Surnud","1151–1217":"1151–1217","1179–1243":"1179–1243","1181–1246":"1181–1246","1192–1251":"1192–1251","1135–1197":"1135–1197","1138–1193":"1138–1193","1197":"1197","1251":"1251","1162":"1162","1151":"1151","1173":"1173","1160":"1160","1193":"1193","1181":"1181","1192":"1192","1180":"1180","1217":"1217","1138":"1138","1246":"1246","1179":"1179","1135":"1135","1243":"1243","1219":"1219","Caulaincourt, 02490, Aisne, Picardie, France":"Caulaincourt, Aisne, Picardie, Prantsusmaa","Caulaincourt, Aisne, Picardie, França":"Caulaincourt, Aisne, Picardie, Prantsusmaa","Caulaincourt, Aisne, Picardie, France":"Caulaincourt, Aisne, Picardie, Prantsusmaa","La Fère, Aisne, Picardie, França":"La Fère, Aisne, Picardie, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1160–1219":"1160–1219","1173–Female":"1173–Kuollut","1151–1217":"1151–1217","1179–1243":"1179–1243","1181–1246":"1181–1246","1192–1251":"1192–1251","1135–1197":"1135–1197","1138–1193":"1138–1193","1197":"1197","1251":"1251","1162":"1162","1151":"1151","1173":"1173","1160":"1160","1193":"1193","1181":"1181","1